HEADWORD: Rescission
<hw>Re*scis"sion</hw> <pr>(r?-s?zh"?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>rescissio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>rescission</ets>. See
<er>Rescind</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of rescinding, abrogating,
annulling, or vacating; <as>as, the <ex>rescission</ex> of a law,
decree, or judgment</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rescissory</ent>⟦br⟧
